# {{ hostname }} Static Site

This scaffold is a minimal static website for `{{ hostname }}` served by nginx behind Traefik.

## Files

- `docker-compose.yml`: nginx service with Traefik labels
- `html/index.html`: starter page content
- `html/favicon.svg`: starter favicon
- `html/assets/css/main.css`: starter stylesheet
- `html/assets/js/main.js`: starter browser script
- `html/assets/images/.gitkeep`: placeholder so the images directory is tracked
- `README.md`: quick notes for the scaffold

## First run

1. Edit `html/index.html` with your real site content.
2. Replace `html/favicon.svg` with your real site favicon when ready.
3. Add your styles to `html/assets/css/main.css` and your scripts to `html/assets/js/main.js`.
4. Put any images or other static media under `html/assets/images/`.
5. Start the stack with `docker compose up -d`.
6. Verify the container becomes healthy and that `https://{{ hostname }}/` serves your static page.

## Runtime behavior

- nginx serves files directly from `./html`
- the generated compose service includes a healthcheck against `http://127.0.0.1/`
- Traefik forwards `{{ hostname }}` to nginx on port `80`
